==English==

===Etymology===
[[w:Old French|Old French]] c.1300 ''genealogie'', from [[w:Vulgar Latin|Late Latin]] ''genealogia'' "tracing of a family", from [[w:Greek Language|Greek]] ''genealogia'', from ''genea'' "generation, descent" + ''logos'' "student of"

===Noun===
'''genealogy''' (Note spelling: not geneology)
# The [[descent]] of a [[person]], [[family]], or [[group]] from an [[ancestor]] or ancestors; [[lineage]] or [[pedigree]].
# A [[record]] or [[table]] of such descent; a [[family tree]].
# The [[study]], and [[formal]] [[recording]] of such descents.

